Vision
"To strive for affordable quality education, while equipping students with knowledge and skills in their chosen stream, teach values, recognize hidden talents, provide opportunities for students to realize their full potential, and thus shape them into future leaders, entrepreneurs, and above all good human beings."
Mission
"To endeavor for quality education and prepare young minds for absorbing knowledge, skills, and sensitivity which would benefit society at large."
Goals
To promote moral and value-based learning
To promote knowledge generation and dissemination
To cultivate the spirit of national development
To nurture inventiveness and empower entrepreneurship
To inculcate sensitivity among the youth towards the community and environment
To create thought-inciting pioneers for the society

data.value: Smt.Saraladevi Satishchandra Agarwal Govt.First Grade CollegeAutonomous, Ballari Campus Code of Conduct for Students  Students should not indulge in any activity which may bring disgrace to the Institution and promise to upkeep the respect of this great institution  Students must abide by all the rules and regulations laid by the College  Students must attend all the classes with at least 75% of attendance in each subject  Students must not be employed anywhere, which affects their regularity to the classes  Students must compulsorily attend the class/class tests/quarterly/mid-term/preparatory examinations conducted in the College  Students should spend their time in the library/reading room during leisure hour and not idle any time in the campus causing disturbance to the class work  Students must stick to deadlines for the submission of Assignments and for presentations  Students should participate in the class work/cultural activities/sports/NCC, NSS activities and abide by the decision of the respective committees  Use of mobile phones within the campus for non-academic purpose is prohibited  Objectionable behaviour within the classroom and during virtual classes shall be viewed seriously  Students should not cause any damage to the property of the college and write or stick any bills or deface them  Students for any misbehaviour  Principal reserves the right to initiate appropriate disciplinary action against misbehaving by students, in consultation with Disciplinary Committee  Students shall obey the board for updates on matters concerning their interest  RAGGING & EVE-TEASING is strictly prohibited within the campus and such acts are punishable under Anti-Ragging Act of  Use of Plastic to be avoided  Use water economically  Switch-off the lights when not in use  Do not waste food  Optimize the use of writing paper  Keep the campus clean & eco-friendly

data.value: Best Practice 1 : Title of the Practice - Career Counseling to Students: Objectives -  To Improve student's Communication skills and overall Personality Development  To help students gain confidence and insight  To guide students to pick the right career  To help in boosting the confidence and morale of the student Context: The majority of college students are from rural areas and lack self-confidence and communication skills. The Career Counselling Cell plays an important role in shaping students' personalities and body language. Practice: The college has held a number of programs and events to help students improve their skill sets, resulting in a positive shift in their skill set. The Institute has a Memorandum of Understanding with Unnati, a skill enhancement center that holds classes in college to help students fill skill gaps. Guest speakers from a variety of fields, such as competitive exams, communication, and personality development, are invited to deliver lectures on various skill development programs. Evidence of Success: Students at the beginning of their degree program are hesitant and lack self-confidence; however, by the end of their degree program, their skill level has greatly improved. The Career Counselling Cell is critical in organizing guest lectures on skill development programs, which result in significant changes in students' learning. The majority of students gain confidence in pursuing their career objectives. Problems Encountered:  There were certain challenges with respect to providing placements to students due to COVID-19.  Shortage of Funds in conducting Placement Drive and Career Counselling Programs.  Since students are prone to losing confidence when things don't go as planned, constant motivation is necessary.  Making students step out of their comfort zone. Best Practice 2 : Title of the Practice - Community Service and Extension Activities Objectives:  Expose students to people who are at a disadvantage (socially, medically, economically, or otherwise)  Help students realize they can make a difference and give them the tools to do so  Develop awareness and a better understanding of the communities they live in  Foster a community of caring and committed individuals Context: Students benefit from participating in community service at a young age in a variety of ways, including Developing a greater sense of social responsibility - a global perspective on society and a desire to 'give back and assist others. Also, it allows students to apply their academic knowledge to real-world situations. Practice: Community service and extension activities are an integral part of students' education. Students of the college are actively involved in community and extension activities from various college bodies like NSS, NCC, Rovers, and Rangers. Community and Extension activities Allow students to apply their academic knowledge to real-world situations. It fosters relationships and social connectedness' while also exposing students to diversity and multiculturalism. Improves communication, interpersonal, and critical thinking skills for life. Also helps students in discovering their passions and interests. Students are involved in Cleaning Drive- Swachh Bharat, NSS Camps in rural areas to create awareness on various societal issues, Rovers and Rangers unit were actively involved in COVID- 19 sanitization drive in college. Evidence of Success:  College and students take great pride in bringing about positive social change through its community and extension activities  Cleanliness drive like Swachh Bharat helps maintain good Health and Hygiene.  National Integration Camp conducted by the college was a huge success as it attracted 50 colleges from the entire South India.  Through annual NSS Camps, social issues in rural regions are made more widely known. Problems Encountered:  Due to the COVID-19 outbreak, Community Service and Extension activities could not be held in 2020 or 2021.  Students' hesitancy to stay back beyond college hours, as the majority of students come from other parts of the district.
